		<font color ="ffffff">
<h2> <center> K-Means Assigned Clusters</center> </h2>	
In the first level instead of supervising and denoted 2 broad groups we used K-mean (k=2) to group the scenes into 2 groups.<br>
The Images were first classified as one of these groups and passed down the pipeline like the manual version.

<center><img src="img/klevel.png" width="600"></center> <br>
The motivation for this approach is that certain scenes are inherently very different from others;
hence if we can initally separate them in diffrent bags and drill down to the fewer possible classes may be we can reduce our errors.<br><br>
Two approaces were employed for the level come classification:<br>
<ol type="1">
	<li><a href="shc_res.html">Manually assigning clusters</a></li>
	<li><a href="shc_res.html">Using K-mean to find similar categories</a></li>
</ol>	 




